1
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,733
<i>You're so stupid!
Don't you ever think?</i>

2
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,800
<i> Why did you let Jeffrey go?</i>

3
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:19,633
<i>I can't stomach what you've been
doing anymore!</i>

4
00:00:20,033 --> 00:00:20,767
<i> I'm done.</i>

5
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:25,000
<i>So you really brought
the cops here?</i>

6
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,667
<i> Enough!</i>

7
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:30,867
<i> Hazel!</i>

8
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:35,400
<i>- Mrs. Cruz, surrender now!
- No, no, please!</i>

9
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:36,967
<i> You've got it wrong! Wait...</i>

10
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:39,767
<i>- Let's go. Cuff her.
- Wait! Alice!</i>

11
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:42,867
<i>- This way, Ma'am.
- Please, wait! Just a second!</i>

12
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:45,500
<i>I spent years forcing myself
to live with Hazel</i>

13
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:47,133
<i> for Jessica's sake.</i>

14
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:49,133
<i>And she wasn't even my real
daughter?</i>

15
00:00:49,267 --> 00:00:54,667
<i>We'll always love Jessica
as family.</i>

16
00:00:54,933 --> 00:00:55,600
<i> What?</i>

17
00:00:55,733 --> 00:00:57,933
<i> You're resigning?</i>

18
00:00:58,067 --> 00:01:00,200
<i>Attorney Salazar,
you can't do that.</i>

19
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:01,733
<i> Hello!</i>

20
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:02,900
<i> Attorney Salazar!</i>

21
00:01:03,567 --> 00:01:04,267
<i> It's over.</i>

22
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,233
<i> Attorney.</i>

23
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:06,933
<i> In case you forgot,</i>

24
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,667
<i>you're facing kidnapping
charges.</i>

25
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:10,400
<i> No bail.</i>

26
00:01:10,533 --> 00:01:12,467
<i>Thank you so much, Ma'am Felma.</i>

27
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:13,633
<i> Sir Manuel.</i>

28
00:01:13,767 --> 00:01:18,233
<i>You had so many chances
to be a father to her.</i>

29
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:19,400
<i> Me?</i>

30
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,033
<i> That'll never happen.</i>

31
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:24,300
<i>You became a father the moment
you chose to help Jeffrey.</i>

32
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:27,000
<i> If you hadn't saved Jeffrey,</i>

33
00:01:27,133 --> 00:01:29,467
<i>who knows what would've happened
to him.</i>

34
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:32,300
<i> Thank you.</i>

35
00:01:47,367 --> 00:01:48,733
<i> You got her pregnant?</i>

36
00:01:48,867 --> 00:01:49,500
<i> Why?</i>

37
00:01:49,633 --> 00:01:51,700
<i> You lied to us!</i>

38
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:54,367
<i>You should've thought
before getting drunk</i>

39
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:56,633
<i> and sleeping with that woman!</i>

40
00:01:56,767 --> 00:01:58,800
<i>I never loved Hazel.
You're the one I love.</i>

41
00:01:58,933 --> 00:02:00,067
<i> You know that.</i>

42
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:05,300
<i>I may have been drunk,
but I'm not stupid.</i>

43
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:31,233
Manuel...

44
00:02:36,267 --> 00:02:37,533
I'm sorry.

45
00:02:39,633 --> 00:02:41,733
Sorry for what?

46
00:02:41,867 --> 00:02:44,400
For doubting your love.

47
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:52,667
Turns out, you and Hazel never
really had a relationship.

48
00:02:52,967 --> 00:02:54,700
Nothing came out of it.

49
00:02:57,633 --> 00:03:01,967
I wouldn't be in that mess if I
hadn't given in to temptation.

50
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:04,900
So yes, I'm still at fault.

51
00:03:05,167 --> 00:03:14,933
I said so many hurtful things
that weren't even true.

52
00:03:16,567 --> 00:03:18,033
Let it go.

53
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:20,533
It's over now.

54
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,867
What matters is that we forgave
each other.

55
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,600
We're okay again.

56
00:03:27,133 --> 00:03:30,333
You know what I'm grateful for?

57
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:34,367
Jessica came into my life.

58
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:38,367
I'll never regret that.

59
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:44,067
She made me feel how to be
a father at a time

60
00:03:44,367 --> 00:03:46,767
when I failed to be one
to our own kids.

61
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:54,733
And you showed her how to be
a real daddy's girl.

62
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:59,000
You were both in the dark about
the truth.

63
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:04,300
Thank you for treating me
like your own child.

64
00:04:04,433 --> 00:04:07,900
<i>Jessica, what are you talking
about?</i>

65
00:04:08,033 --> 00:04:09,467
<i> You are my daughter.</i>

66
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:12,433
<i>And I love you so much.
You know that.</i>

67
00:04:12,733 --> 00:04:14,433
<i> Please forgive me.</i>

68
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:16,300
<i> Mommy and me.</i>

69
00:04:16,433 --> 00:04:18,600
<i> Please forgive us, Dad.</i>

70
00:04:19,033 --> 00:04:22,000
Did Jessica ever find out she
wasn't my real daughter?

71
00:04:23,667 --> 00:04:26,867
Maybe that's why she keeps
apologizing in my dreams.

72
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:39,300
<i>- Here. Caldereta. Chopsuey.
- Yes.</i>

73
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:49,067
Wow!

74
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,967
Egg pie.

75
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:52,933
Dad.

76
00:04:54,933 --> 00:04:58,133
Dad, sorry if we judged you
before.

77
00:04:58,267 --> 00:05:01,467
We really thought you
and Hazel had an affair,

78
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:04,233
and that's why you had a child
with her.

79
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:06,467
You don't need to apologize.

80
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,267
None of this is your fault.

81
00:05:12,767 --> 00:05:14,100
Don't be sad.

82
00:05:15,567 --> 00:05:17,100
That's why I asked Didang
to cook.

83
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:19,367
So we could celebrate.

84
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:25,000
And thank God Jeffrey is safe.

85
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:27,633
You're all safe, my children.

86
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:31,167
And of course,
if Jessica were still alive,

87
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:34,267
she'd definitely be celebrating
with us.

88
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:43,467
There.

89
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:47,000
Jessica's with us now.

90
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:50,400
Nice one. Good thinking, Coleen.

91
00:05:50,533 --> 00:05:51,867
Really good.

92
00:05:53,933 --> 00:05:55,600
Andeng,

93
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:56,667
you okay?

94
00:05:57,867 --> 00:05:59,333
Yeah, I'm fine.

95
00:06:01,367 --> 00:06:04,267
I was just thinking about Joel.

96
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:11,000
He'd be happy if he were here
with us.

97
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:14,467
But I'm glad you're here now,
bro.

98
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,633
Of course.
I'm just glad you're safe.

99
00:06:17,833 --> 00:06:19,367
Sorry, Mom. Dad.

100
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:26,000
I just can't help thinking
about Joel.

101
00:06:26,133 --> 00:06:28,533
And what Hazel did to him.

102
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:35,767
I can't have peace knowing Hazel
hasn't suffered yet.

103
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:38,967
Knowing she's still free.

104
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:47,267
I won't rest until I make
that woman face what she did.

105
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:48,700
Jeff...

106
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,400
Cruz, you have a visitor.

107
00:06:59,733 --> 00:07:00,800
I don't want to.

108
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:02,933
I don't want to see anyone.

109
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,333
Send them away.

110
00:07:08,967 --> 00:07:10,500
You're a devil, Hazel!

111
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:13,967
You lied to me for years!

112
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,400
Jessica wasn't even my real
daughter!

113
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:29,900
So you know now?

114
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,467
What's your problem?

115
00:07:34,933 --> 00:07:37,967
Didn't Jessica love you
with everything she had?

116
00:07:38,233 --> 00:07:40,167
You two were inseparable.

117
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:43,300
So what are you so mad about?

118
00:07:43,767 --> 00:07:46,333
That's exactly the point!

119
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:49,800
Hazel, you destroyed my family!

120
00:07:49,967 --> 00:07:51,967
You made me believe I got you
pregnant,

121
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:54,967
then dumped Jojo's
responsibility on me!

122
00:07:56,567 --> 00:08:00,967
Is it my fault you're an idiot?

123
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:02,833
You're stupid.

124
00:08:02,967 --> 00:08:04,633
Why didn't you count the months?

125
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:08,333
You know what? You're not just
stupid with numbers.

126
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,433
You're stupid in life.

127
00:08:10,567 --> 00:08:15,100
That's why you're still hiding
under your mistress's skirt.

128
00:08:15,233 --> 00:08:16,967
You really are something else.

129
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,667
You used Manuel,

130
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,133
and you still have the nerve
to insult him.

131
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:28,833
Life in prison isn't enough
for you.

132
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:33,700
You deserve the electric chair.

133
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:35,767
Hang upside down.

134
00:08:37,467 --> 00:08:39,500
Feed to crocodiles.

135
00:08:41,267 --> 00:08:43,633
You're a servant of Satan,
Hazel.

136
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:48,333
You're worse than the devil
himself!

137
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:50,133
Darn you!

138
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:54,733
Let go of me!

139
00:08:56,967 --> 00:08:59,733
We suffered for years.

140
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:05,100
Years believing all your lies.

141
00:09:05,467 --> 00:09:08,500
You destroyed my marriage
with Manuel.

142
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:12,267
Our dreams.

143
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:14,433
You destroyed my family!

144
00:09:15,467 --> 00:09:16,633
Let go of me!

145
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:19,100
- Come here!
- Let me go.

146
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:21,833
Come here! That's not enough!

147
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,500
Not enough!

148
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:28,433
That's still not enough
for everything we sacrificed

149
00:09:30,667 --> 00:09:33,400
for you just so you could get
everything you wanted!

150
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:40,833
The kids grew up without
a father for years.

151
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:43,367
They learned to hate him.

152
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:47,133
They were bullied at school.

153
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:51,600
Jeffrey almost went to prison.

154
00:09:53,267 --> 00:09:56,433
While you were out there,

155
00:09:56,700 --> 00:10:02,033
living the life with the man
who should've been my husband!

156
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:07,300
You're evil! You're a monster!

157
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:11,400
There's nothing you can do
because you're also stupid.

158
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:13,167
Hear that?

159
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:15,400
That's why you and Manuel
are perfect for each other.

160
00:10:15,533 --> 00:10:17,967
Because you're both idiots.

161
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,967
That's who you are.

162
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:21,533
And now...

163
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:26,067
you're going after my kids?

164
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:31,300
You're going to kill them too?
Like what you did to Joel?

165
00:10:32,867 --> 00:10:34,267
What are you talking about?

166
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:37,267
I know the truth down
to the bone.

167
00:10:38,633 --> 00:10:44,967
We all know you injected Joel
with those drugs.

168
00:10:45,367 --> 00:10:50,700
You had Coleen and Andrea
harassed.

169
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,400
You're evil!

170
00:10:53,533 --> 00:10:55,500
You're disgusting!
You little demon!

171
00:10:55,633 --> 00:10:57,667
- I don't know anything.
- Devil!

172
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,100
You're just making things up.

173
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:00,300
I don't know
what you're talking about!

174
00:11:00,433 --> 00:11:02,633
Boss! Sir!

175
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:05,400
Get these people out of here!
They're attacking me!

176
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:07,300
Is this even allowed?

177
00:11:07,533 --> 00:11:08,500
Boss!

178
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:13,033
I promise you, Hazel.

179
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:19,833
You will pay for everything
you did to my family.

180
00:11:19,967 --> 00:11:23,233
We're filing case after case
against you.

181
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:26,000
You'll rot in prison.

182
00:11:26,133 --> 00:11:32,133
Your body will decay here,
and so will your soul.

183
00:11:32,267 --> 00:11:36,800
An endless fire
will burn you in hell.

184
00:11:39,067 --> 00:11:40,633
I swear it.

185
00:11:46,933 --> 00:11:47,967
Manuel...

186
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:51,600
Manuel, I love you so much.

187
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:55,767
Manuel, I just...

188
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,700
Manuel, I only...

189
00:12:17,067 --> 00:12:18,767
Alice.

190
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:21,233
Thank you for meeting me.

191
00:12:21,367 --> 00:12:23,067
Are you going into hiding now?

192
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:25,933
Word is, you're resigning.

193
00:12:26,067 --> 00:12:27,400
Yes.

194
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,567
But I'm not running.

195
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:32,967
Aren't you scared the police
might come after you next?

196
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:34,400
How about you, Alice?

197
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,367
Aren't you afraid?

198
00:12:38,667 --> 00:12:41,567
Why would I be?
I didn't do anything wrong.

199
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:43,567
Alice,

200
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:47,533
you were involved
in Joel Santiago's death.

201
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:52,000
You knew who killed him.

202
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,300
But you chose to stay silent.

203
00:13:04,933 --> 00:13:07,600
I only committed one sin
against you, Manuel.

204
00:13:09,367 --> 00:13:11,800
But you destroyed
my entire life.

205
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,433
I lost my husband.

206
00:13:20,367 --> 00:13:22,233
You even killed my child.

207
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,567
But I won't let this end here.

208
00:13:29,467 --> 00:13:31,967
I won't let everything come
to nothing.

209
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:35,767
I still have a card left.

210
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,767
I still have one move to play.

211
00:13:41,867 --> 00:13:43,433
And I guarantee you.

212
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:48,333
I will win.

213
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,233
So, Mom, how many times
did you slap that woman?

214
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,700
Three, Mom?

215
00:13:55,867 --> 00:13:58,867
One for Jeff, one for me,
and one for Andrea?

216
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,433
Mom, we all
should've been there.

217
00:14:01,567 --> 00:14:02,600
Full force.

218
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:03,433
She wouldn't have stood
a chance.

219
00:14:03,567 --> 00:14:05,233
Oh, dear, that wasn't necessary.

220
00:14:05,367 --> 00:14:06,267
Your mom was possessed

221
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,633
like some kind
of warrior spirit.

222
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:10,600
Against her alone,
Hazel didn't stand a chance.

223
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:12,633
But you know...

224
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:14,900
I kind of pity her, too.

225
00:14:15,033 --> 00:14:16,967
Mom, there you go again.

226
00:14:19,167 --> 00:14:20,233
Think about it.

227
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:22,833
What kind of life
did Hazel really have?

228
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,467
What was her childhood like?

229
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:30,233
How much pain and sadness
did she go through

230
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:33,567
to turn out that bitter?

231
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:37,333
She wouldn't have done
all that if she'd been happy.

232
00:14:38,433 --> 00:14:41,167
Yes, but that still doesn't give
her the right to hurt people.

233
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:43,867
To destroy Jessica's life,
our family.

234
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:45,400
Dad's right.

235
00:14:45,533 --> 00:14:46,900
She could've chosen
to be a good person, Mom.

236
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:48,567
But she didn't.

237
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:50,267
What you did was right, Mom.

238
00:14:51,067 --> 00:14:53,400
She deserves to pay
for everything

239
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:55,633
she did to our family.

240
00:14:55,767 --> 00:14:58,367
Maybe then,
she'll finally learn.

241
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:09,833
Jessica, my child.

242
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:14,267
We lost so much time.

243
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:17,800
I never got to rock you
to sleep.

244
00:15:19,033 --> 00:15:22,533
Never heard your first word.

245
00:15:24,033 --> 00:15:28,733
I didn't see your first steps.

246
00:15:30,167 --> 00:15:37,467
So many birthdays,
so many special days lost.

247
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:42,767
I hope you forgive your papa.

248
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:45,867
I hope you forgive
your mama, too.

249
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:49,733
Your Daddy Manuel
raised you well.

250
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:55,500
I know you'll like
what I'm about to do.

251
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:58,700
And I know you'll forgive me.

252
00:16:01,933 --> 00:16:03,800
I love you so much, my child.

253
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:10,233
I love you, my Jessica.

254
00:16:20,867 --> 00:16:22,267
I'm sorry, dear.

255
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:26,800
I'm so sorry.

256
00:16:30,633 --> 00:16:35,400
I'm ready to cooperate with you
against Hazel, Sir, Ma'am.

257
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,800
Thank you so much, Jojo.

258
00:16:38,933 --> 00:16:42,133
This will help our family
finally get justice.

259
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:48,067
I also thank you for helping
a family very dear to me.

260
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:50,533
But a word of warning, though.

261
00:16:52,733 --> 00:16:54,633
Just because
you're cooperating...

262
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:56,767
doesn't mean
you're off the hook.

263
00:16:57,767 --> 00:17:01,033
You still have to answer
for what you did.

264
00:17:04,267 --> 00:17:05,300
Right, Attorney?

265
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,433
That's correct, Sir Noah.

266
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:11,367
I understand.

267
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,900
I still have legal
responsibility.

268
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:19,700
Oh, I have discussed your case
with my associate.

269
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:20,933
Attorney Llagas.

270
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:23,233
He'll be representing you.

271
00:17:23,367 --> 00:17:26,400
No offense, Attorney Llagas,

272
00:17:26,533 --> 00:17:28,800
but why do we need
another lawyer?

273
00:17:28,933 --> 00:17:30,967
Why not you, Attorney?

274
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:33,700
Conflict of interest.

275
00:17:33,933 --> 00:17:39,000
I represent you as the offended
party in this case.

276
00:17:39,133 --> 00:17:45,233
One lawyer can't stand
on both sides of justice.

277
00:17:45,367 --> 00:17:48,533
Jojo Cañares must surrender
to the police

278
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:51,067
and fully cooperate
in the investigation.

279
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:54,967
That can be considered
a mitigating circumstance

280
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:57,300
to reduce his sentence.

281
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:20,767
I was the one who gave Hazel
Jeffrey's flight details.

282
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:24,200
That's how the kidnappers
found him.

283
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,367
<i> What time is your flight?</i>

284
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,900
<i> This Saturday.</i>

285
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:30,700
<i>I arrive at one
in the afternoon.</i>

286
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:33,000
<i>Saturday, one in the afternoon.</i>

287
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:36,167
<i>Thank you for giving me
his flight details.</i>

288
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:37,867
<i>Pretty satisfying to watch, huh?</i>

289
00:18:39,733 --> 00:18:44,333
I was also involved
in Joel's death.

290
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:54,833
Hazel told me to leave her.

291
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:59,300
I only found out later
that Joel was dead.

292
00:19:03,233 --> 00:19:04,367
Felma, why?

293
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:08,267
This feels exactly like

294
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,533
what we went through
with Coleen before.

295
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,033
What if Hazel
does something again?

296
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:17,167
Felma, don't worry.

297
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:20,600
This won't end in some deal
like last time.

298
00:19:20,733 --> 00:19:23,467
I promise you,
Hazel is going to prison.

299
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:25,733
Nothing's going to stop that.

300
00:19:44,533 --> 00:19:45,567
Jessica...

301
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:48,700
thank you
for coming into our lives.

302
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:52,333
I'm sorry for all the mistakes
I made.

303
00:19:53,967 --> 00:19:55,267
I may not have said it enough,

304
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:59,100
but I was really happy
you showed me

305
00:19:59,233 --> 00:20:01,400
what it's like to have
a younger sister.

306
00:20:03,033 --> 00:20:04,800
Jessica, even when we weren't
okay before,

307
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,700
the truth is,

308
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:08,833
I'm grateful

309
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:11,067
you took care of Dad for us.

310
00:20:12,467 --> 00:20:15,867
I'm sorry, Jessica.

311
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,333
I'm sorry again to you...

312
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:21,033
I didn't accept you
as my sister right away.

313
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:26,033
Thank you for being patient
with me anyway.

314
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:30,300
You gave me love even
when I didn't deserve it.

315
00:20:32,233 --> 00:20:38,233
I wish you were here to see
that we're whole again

316
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,933
as a family.

317
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,167
Nothing's changed, Jessica.

318
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:48,733
Whether you're related to Manuel
by blood or not

319
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:52,900
I've always treated you
like my own child.

320
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:56,800
It's like you came straight
from my womb, my child.

321
00:20:57,900 --> 00:21:02,833
Thank you for treating me
like your second mother.

322
00:21:04,933 --> 00:21:06,533
Jessica...

323
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:10,900
thank you for all
the beautiful memories.

324
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:15,000
You brought light into my life

325
00:21:15,133 --> 00:21:18,367
when everything was dark.

326
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:23,067
You gave me a reason
to keep going, my dear.

327
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:27,267
You made me feel
how to be a father.

328
00:21:30,300 --> 00:21:32,267
Jessica, I know
I'm not perfect...

329
00:21:33,867 --> 00:21:37,667
but you accepted me
despite my flaws.

330
00:21:38,667 --> 00:21:40,467
<i> I got your mom pregnant.</i>

331
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:43,167
<i>The laws in Saudi Arabia
were very strict.</i>

332
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:45,567
<i> So I wasn't born out of love?</i>

333
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:48,933
<i>You got mom pregnant
and only married her</i>

334
00:21:49,067 --> 00:21:50,667
<i> because of some law?</i>

335
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,400
<i> Dad!</i>

336
00:21:52,533 --> 00:21:55,000
And most of all,
you took care of me

337
00:21:55,133 --> 00:21:57,467
when I couldn't even stand

338
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,300
or move on my own.

339
00:21:59,433 --> 00:22:00,900
You never left me.

340
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:07,400
<i>Dear, I'm sorry if I've been
a burden to you and your mom.</i>

341
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:09,133
<i> Please don't think that.</i>

342
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:11,067
<i>You'll never be a burden to me.</i>

343
00:22:12,467 --> 00:22:13,867
That love...

344
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:16,267
that's what inspired me

345
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:19,000
to be a good father
to your siblings.

346
00:22:21,533 --> 00:22:23,767
I will never forget you,
Jessica.

347
00:22:25,633 --> 00:22:27,367
Even if you didn't come from me,

348
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:30,933
you are still my child,
nothing has changed.

349
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:36,067
You will stay in my heart
forever, my dear.

350
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,833
I love you so much, my child.

351
00:22:44,867 --> 00:22:46,733
Love you so, so much.

352
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,467
You animal!

353
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,267
What the hell
are you talking about?

354
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:05,200
I had nothing to do with what
happened to Jeffrey or Joel!

355
00:23:05,333 --> 00:23:08,200
- You're a liar! Liar!
- Stop denying it, Hazel!

356
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:10,000
Just admit the truth!

357
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:11,833
Admit what?

358
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:14,133
It's not true,
so I have nothing to admit!

359
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:15,167
Liar!

360
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:17,067
Don't listen to him!
He's a liar!

361
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,700
It's over, Hazel.

362
00:23:18,933 --> 00:23:20,533
You're such a jerk.

363
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:24,000
I thought when you came back
into our lives,

364
00:23:24,133 --> 00:23:25,567
you'd make things right.

365
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:27,767
But look at what you did!

366
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:31,267
Then again, you already
abandoned us back then.

367
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,800
So what more now
that our child is dead?

368
00:23:34,067 --> 00:23:35,833
You're completely worthless.

369
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,033
A coward!

370
00:23:37,533 --> 00:23:38,933
I'm not a coward!

371
00:23:39,067 --> 00:23:41,400
This is the bravest thing
I've ever done.

372
00:23:41,533 --> 00:23:43,333
Fixing my mistakes

373
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:47,100
and turning you
in for your evil.

374
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:48,567
You're the coward!

375
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:50,433
Because you can't even
admit to yourself

376
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:52,467
how horrible you really are!

377
00:23:52,833 --> 00:23:54,567
You're the worthless one!

378
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:57,300
It's only right
that we lost our child.

379
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:00,700
Because you were never capable
of being a good mother to her!

380
00:24:00,833 --> 00:24:02,433
That's enough!

381
00:24:02,567 --> 00:24:03,633
- Take it back!
- That's the truth!

382
00:24:03,767 --> 00:24:05,333
No! You deserve to rot in jail!

383
00:24:05,467 --> 00:24:07,433
You're the one who should rot
in prison, do you hear me?

384
00:24:07,567 --> 00:24:08,967
Get out of here!
Get out!

385
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:11,733
You animal!
You're disgusting!

386
00:24:11,867 --> 00:24:13,633
You have no shame!

387
00:24:13,767 --> 00:24:15,433
You animal!

388
00:24:15,567 --> 00:24:16,900
Rot in prison!

389
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:29,700
What are you doing here?

390
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:31,300
I just wanted to see you

391
00:24:31,433 --> 00:24:33,900
For the last time.

392
00:24:37,933 --> 00:24:38,900
Jojo, wait.

393
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:44,167
This is my favorite picture
of Jessica.

394
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:46,167
Please take care of it,
the way I've taken care of it

395
00:24:46,300 --> 00:24:47,633
for almost two decades.

396
00:24:50,033 --> 00:24:51,667
Come on, let's celebrate!

397
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:54,900
Sir Manuel and I have
somewhere to go, Ma'am.

398
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:56,433
We're heading to the RTC

399
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:58,867
to file the annulment against
Hazel.
